        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Average vandalism incident costs $25,000-50,000 including repairs, cleanup, delays, and increased insurance. Graffiti removal alone averages $5,000-15,000 per incident."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What types of vandalism affect construction sites?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Common vandalism includes graffiti/tagging, equipment damage, window breaking, arson attempts, dumping, fence cutting, and destruction of completed work. Weekend vandalism is most common."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How effective is surveillance at preventing vandalism?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Sites with visible surveillance experience 75-90% reduction in vandalism. Active monitoring with audio warnings stops most vandals immediately, while recorded evidence ensures prosecution."
      }
    }
  ]
});
